<D>__{i got the early edition! it was just dropped off at the newsstand.}
<C>__{ed}
<P>__{(he smiles at everyone)}
<D>__{this is the big moment...!}
<A>__{ed opens the paper to the entertainment page. insert the newspaper. ed turns to a column, "the theatrical life, by victor crowley." under this is a photograph of an old man with an ascot.}
<B>__{wide}
<A>__{everybody excitedly crowds around and starts reading. a moment... and then their faces drop. clearly, this is a disastrous review. their faces get sadder, and sadder... and then they finish. a melancholy beat, until }
<C>__{bunny}
<D>__{what does that old queen know? he wasn't even there!}
<P>__{(he knocks back a drink)}
<D>__{sending a copy boy to do his dirty work. well fuck him !}
